-->

- Closes #14525

### User facing changelog

- Added the ability to match on `resourceType` with `cy.intercept()`, and to see the resource type of an intercepted request as `req.resourceType`.

### Additional details

- All browsers report this in pre-request information to enable proxy logging, so we can now safely add it in the public `intercept` API too.
- In combination with `cy.intercept(..., { log: false }`, users can disable/enable logs by resource type: https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress/issues/9358

### Steps to test

Use the new `resourceType` property on `RouteMatcher` and `req` to match only certain requests:

```ts
cy.intercept({ resourceType: 'style' }) // only CSS

cy.intercept('/my-api', (req) => {
  expect(req.resourceType).to.eq('xmlhttprequest') // only XHRs should hit the API
})
```

- Closes #14525

### User facing changelog

- Added the ability to match on `resourceType` with `cy.intercept()`, and to see the resource type of an intercepted request as `req.resourceType`.

### Additional details

- All browsers report this in pre-request information to enable proxy logging, so we can now safely add it in the public `intercept` API too.
- In combination with `cy.intercept(..., { log: false }`, users can disable/enable logs by resource type: https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress/issues/9358

### Steps to test

Use the new `resourceType` property on `RouteMatcher` and `req` to match only certain requests:

```ts
cy.intercept({ resourceType: 'style' }) // only CSS

cy.intercept('/my-api', (req) => {
  expect(req.resourceType).to.eq('xmlhttprequest') // only XHRs should hit the API
})

- Closes #14525

### User facing changelog

- Added the ability to match on `resourceType` with `cy.intercept()`, and to see the resource type of an intercepted request as `req.resourceType`.

### Additional details

- All browsers report this in pre-request information to enable proxy logging, so we can now safely add it in the public `intercept` API too.
- In combination with `cy.intercept(..., { log: false }`, users can disable/enable logs by resource type: https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress/issues/9358

### Steps to test

Use the new `resourceType` property on `RouteMatcher` and `req` to match only certain requests:

```ts
cy.intercept({ resourceType: 'style' }) // only CSS

cy.intercept('/my-api', (req) => {
  expect(req.resourceType).to.eq('xmlhttprequest') // only XHRs should hit the API
})
```
